#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.24:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Gahapativagga "
msgstr "3. Householders "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Dutiyahatthakasutta → hatthakāḷavakasaṅgahavatthusuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Dutiyahatthakasutta "
msgstr "24. With Hatthaka (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.219, sc1
msgctxt "an8.24:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Āḷavī, at the Aggāḷava Tree-shrine. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho hatthako āḷavako pañcamattehi upāsakasatehi parivuto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho hatthakaṃ āḷavakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the householder Hatthaka of Āḷavī, escorted by around five hundred lay followers, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to Hatthaka: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.24:1.3"
msgid "“mahatī kho tyāyaṃ, hatthaka, parisā. "
msgstr "“Hatthaka, you have a large congregation. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, hatthaka, imaṃ mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgaṇhāsī”ti? "
msgstr "How do you bring together such a large congregation?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: tehāhaṃ → tenāhaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.24:1.5"
msgid "“Yānimāni, bhante, bhagavatā desitāni cattāri saṅgahavatthūni, tehāhaṃ imaṃ mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgaṇhāmi. "
msgstr "“Sir, I bring together such a large congregation by using the four ways of being inclusive as taught by the Buddha. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhante, yaṃ jānāmi: "
msgstr "When I know that a person "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.7"
msgid "‘ayaṃ dānena saṅgahetabbo’ti, taṃ dānena saṅgaṇhāmi; "
msgstr "can be included by a gift, I include them by giving a gift. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.8"
msgid "yaṃ jānāmi: "
msgstr "When I know that a person "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.9"
msgid "‘ayaṃ peyyavajjena saṅgahetabbo’ti, taṃ peyyavajjena saṅgaṇhāmi; "
msgstr "can be included by kindly words, I include them by kindly words. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.10"
msgid "yaṃ jānāmi: "
msgstr "When I know that a person "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.11"
msgid "‘ayaṃ atthacariyāya saṅgahetabbo’ti, taṃ atthacariyāya saṅgaṇhāmi; "
msgstr "can be included by taking care of them, I include them by caring for them. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.12"
msgid "yaṃ jānāmi: "
msgstr "When I know that a person "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.13"
msgid "‘ayaṃ samānattatāya saṅgahetabbo’ti, taṃ samānattatāya saṅgaṇhāmi. "
msgstr "can be included by equality, I include them by treating them equally. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.14"
msgid "Saṃvijjanti kho pana me, bhante, kule bhogā. "
msgstr "But also, sir, my family is wealthy. "

# NOTE: This is a very honest acknowledgement of privilege.
msgctxt "an8.24:1.15"
msgid "Daliddassa kho no tathā sotabbaṃ maññantī”ti. "
msgstr "They wouldn’t think that a poor person was worth listening to in the same way.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.24:1.16"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, hatthaka. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Hatthaka! "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.17"
msgid "Yoni kho tyāyaṃ, hatthaka, mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgahetuṃ. "
msgstr "This is the right way to bring together a large congregation. "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.18"
msgid "Ye hi keci, hatthaka, atītamaddhānaṃ mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgahesuṃ, sabbe te imeheva catūhi saṅgahavatthūhi mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Whether in the past, future, or present, all those who have brought together a large congregation have done so by using these four ways of being inclusive.” "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.19"
msgid "Yepi hi keci, hatthaka, anāgatamaddhānaṃ mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgaṇhissanti, sabbe te imeheva catūhi saṅgahavatthūhi mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgaṇhissanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.24:1.20"
msgid "Yepi hi keci, hatthaka, etarahi mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgaṇhanti, sabbe te imeheva catūhi saṅgahavatthūhi mahatiṃ parisaṃ saṅgaṇhantī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.220, sc2
msgctxt "an8.24:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho hatthako āḷavako bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired Hatthaka of Āḷavī with a Dhamma talk, after which he got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha before leaving. "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkante hatthake āḷavake bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, not long after Hatthaka had left, the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.3"
msgid "“aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgataṃ hatthakaṃ āḷavakaṃ dhāretha. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, you should remember the householder Hatthaka of Āḷavī as someone who has eight amazing and incredible qualities. "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.4"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi? "
msgstr "What eight? "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.5"
msgid "Saddho, bhikkhave, hatthako āḷavako; "
msgstr "He’s faithful, "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.6"
msgid "sīlavā, bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "ethical, "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.7"
msgid "hirīmā … "
msgstr "conscientious, "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.8"
msgid "ottappī … "
msgstr "prudent, "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.9"
msgid "bahussuto … "
msgstr "learned, "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.10"
msgid "cāgavā … "
msgstr "generous, "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.11"
msgid "paññavā, bhikkhave, hatthako āḷavako; "
msgstr "wise, "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.12"
msgid "appiccho, bhikkhave, hatthako āḷavako. "
msgstr "and has few wishes. "

msgctxt "an8.24:2.13"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi acchariyehi abbhutehi dhammehi samannāgataṃ hatthakaṃ āḷavakaṃ dhārethā”ti. "
msgstr "You should remember the householder Hatthaka of Āḷavī as someone who has these eight amazing and incredible qualities.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.24:2.14"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

